Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.31,0:00:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was starting to say, I got this letter about criticizing how I was handling the,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.86,0:00:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or presented during a lecture, I guess, to transcend thinkingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.36,0:01:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and pointing out that in classic Buddhism, there's 32 steps or something to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.50,0:01:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the answer to that is you don't have to transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.79,0:01:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to understand the mind in order to understand the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.90,0:01:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're not the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.43,0:01:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And, besides, the source of thinkingness is an infinite silence,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.90,0:01:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the substrate of the mind, which is present.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.00,0:01:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, nobody would be able to hear me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.78,0:01:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because your mind is silent, you can hear what's being said.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.57,0:01:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are is the matrix, the silence that exists the instant prior to a thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.04,0:01:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,not in a horizontal fashion, but in a surface fashion,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.89,0:02:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if you give up being fascinated, the narcissistic investment in your thinkingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.73,0:02:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and devalue it, see it as sort of a hindrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.79,0:02:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say, how can I make the mind stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.18,0:02:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I get beyond this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.15,0:02:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to make the mind stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.12,0:02:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even have to understand anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.12,0:02:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point in 32 years of meditation on the various stages of transcending the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.52,0:02:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because the mind has no existence and no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.59,0:02:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only catching.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you begin to live in the field, so this morning we're talking about being the field
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.74,0:02:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the content of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.18,0:02:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to witness that everything is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.36,0:02:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When you stop projecting res cogitans upon res externa,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.37,0:02:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you will stop seeing out there what you have projected out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.83,0:02:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to think about.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.90,0:02:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening spontaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.93,0:02:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of that which it has become.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.75,0:03:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.84,0:03:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't cause other things to happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.22,0:03:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a consequence of that which it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.21,0:03:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we see what we call motion or change about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.80,0:03:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's also projection, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.50,0:03:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.91,0:03:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you'll notice the first thing about the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.31,0:03:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say I would like to be considerate of others
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.19,0:03:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of always,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.02,0:03:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to be loving and considerate of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.30,0:03:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can think about it from now for the next 40 years
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.56,0:03:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will not diminish it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.74,0:03:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.00,0:03:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.86,0:03:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You bypass the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.25,0:03:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point in mastering the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.09,0:03:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You just bypass it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.78,0:03:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.58,0:03:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the field of that which you aspire to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.53,0:04:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't think about being nice to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.80,0:04:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.03,0:04:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You choose that that is what you value.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.19,0:04:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you become the expression of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.81,0:04:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as you become the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.41,0:04:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,its expression in the linear domain is automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.54,0:04:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to think about what to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.50,0:04:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The bird goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.33,0:04:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.33,0:04:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what's to think about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.18,0:04:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the automatic response of isness with isness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.62,0:04:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of joy with joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.12,0:04:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way of life, acknowledging life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.29,0:04:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't require any thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.88,0:04:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't require separateness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.88,0:04:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an automatic consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.94,0:04:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't involve thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.37,0:04:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way you're being in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.37,0:04:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you are, what you've chosen,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.56,0:04:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,what you've chosen to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.66,0:04:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you choose to be something,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.66,0:05:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to pull to it that which is appropriate to that way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.42,0:05:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.89,0:05:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought to respond to the bird with knock-knock was automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.31,0:05:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It was spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.04,0:05:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, as you catch the spontaneity,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.24,0:05:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as you identify more with the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.55,0:05:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to catch that everything is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.43,0:05:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.82,0:05:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That even the decision to be deliberate is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.23,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't deliberately decide to be deliberate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You just said,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.70,0:05:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll be deliberate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.70,0:05:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It just came out of nothing, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.42,0:05:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to take credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.42,0:05:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you don't have to take credit,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.42,0:05:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,nor do you have to disparage yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.42,0:05:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you get out of the moralistic, ethical dialogue with yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.93,0:05:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which entertains people for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.94,0:06:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.23,0:06:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty years later, you're still puzzling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.23,0:06:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no answer to it because the mind is very clever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.23,0:06:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego, in order to survive, will create conundrums faster than you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.23,0:06:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Faster than you can solve them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.23,0:06:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Faster than you can solve them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.42,0:06:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you're getting paid to solve them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.83,0:06:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in which case it will take you quite a while to solve them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.05,0:06:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,At 75 an hour, it would take me a couple of years to psychoanalyze you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.05,0:06:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was in psychoanalysis, I got a special reduced rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.01,0:06:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was $20 an hour by the leading professor of Columbia Psychoanalytic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.06,0:06:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,$20 an hour, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.06,0:06:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it took four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.06,0:06:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But the value every day of the week.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.22,0:06:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the value was
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.22,0:06:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that you stop projecting into the world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and you own what Freud called the id.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.22,0:07:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's popular to put down Freud and the edible complex and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.22,0:07:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.22,0:07:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Great mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.69,0:07:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what he said is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.69,0:07:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you own a thing, you're going to repress it or project it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.69,0:07:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you're going to deny it and isolate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.99,0:07:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And isolate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see isolation, interestingly, in history, in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed we came across some very interesting examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.08,0:07:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This solves some political problems of many a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.08,0:07:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We find out that some people,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.18,0:07:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we got two different calibration numbers on the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.18,0:07:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the greatest political conundrums of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.18,0:07:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We solved it the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.62,0:07:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, one day I'll get he's at.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.62,0:07:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we get him at?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.05,0:07:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget his name even.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.26,0:07:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the book anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.26,0:07:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, one of the great political discussions of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.26,0:07:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which is still unresolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.26,0:07:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we got him one time at 420 or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.26,0:07:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And another time I got him like at 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:08:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, oh, what is this here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.26,0:08:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happened to us a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.52,0:08:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially in double agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.52,0:08:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They can compartmentalize.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.52,0:08:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guy you know and think highly of,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.75,0:08:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world honors,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.75,0:08:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in this particular case, he was quite prominent,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.75,0:08:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated, you know, 420.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.51,0:08:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.77,0:08:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,he was secretly an espionage agent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and selling all our secrets to Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.77,0:08:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How could a guy who calibrates at 420
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.77,0:08:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,sell secrets to Russia and create the whole,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.77,0:08:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because those duplicitous people in World War II
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.77,0:08:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the nuclear thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.77,0:08:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or why we went through the whole Cold War.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.77,0:08:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we set up the whole Cold War.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.77,0:08:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fear of nuclear energy, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.77,0:08:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's triggered current events.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.77,0:08:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the fear they're going to get the nuclear power.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.77,0:08:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.22,0:08:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the negative fallout of this is enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.22,0:08:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we couldn't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.22,0:08:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:08:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't that familiar with that amount of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.22,0:09:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Brock looked it up on the computer for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.22,0:09:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We got the history of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.32,0:09:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And politically, it didn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.53,0:09:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a guy that supposedly,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.53,0:09:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and they never did really resolve it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.53,0:09:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that sold the most important secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that we had to the Russians.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, he was a respectable, prominent person.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.66,0:09:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we got,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.66,0:09:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so then when we got,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.66,0:09:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,he calibrated, I think, at 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.66,0:09:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure about the numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.66,0:09:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They're in the book, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.74,0:09:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We found compartmentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.74,0:09:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Compartmentalization is not really well known in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.74,0:09:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It explains the nice guy who murders his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.74,0:09:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a really wonderful guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.74,0:09:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And then she gets pregnant and he kills her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.74,0:09:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of duplicities now suddenly make,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.74,0:09:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,espionage agents,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.74,0:09:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the Manhattan Project,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.74,0:09:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the great scientists there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.74,0:09:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How did they manage to do
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.74,0:09:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,what they did, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.74,0:09:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you'll find they've got two numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.74,0:09:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They're compartmentalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.89,0:09:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've run across it a couple times in personal life
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.89,0:10:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,where somebody wanted to come and see us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.89,0:10:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We got with the arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.89,0:10:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.89,0:10:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next time we did it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.89,0:10:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we got, no, he's like 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.89,0:10:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And frankly, he'd like to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.89,0:10:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.89,0:10:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, compartmentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A person can literally have two personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.50,0:10:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So many of the ambiguities of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.50,0:10:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How can such a wonderful person
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.50,0:10:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,like this, this, this, do what they did?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.50,0:10:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because that personality didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.50,0:10:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The other actually did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.50,0:10:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So society wonders if multiple personality
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.95,0:10:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is a psychiatric fantasy or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.95,0:10:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm not calling them multiple personalities,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but people can compartmentalize
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.95,0:10:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so that one part is this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.01,0:10:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll read about the respectable married man
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.01,0:10:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with five children who goes to work every day
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.01,0:10:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's also a serial murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.01,0:10:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's murdered 20 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.01,0:10:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Green killer murderer or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.01,0:10:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And how could he be a respectable guy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.01,0:10:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with a family and four kids
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.01,0:10:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and murdered 23 people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.01,0:10:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this personality went to work
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.13,0:10:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and was responsible,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.13,0:11:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but this one was a vicious killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.13,0:11:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.13,0:11:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you own within yourself the downside,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.13,0:11:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to compartmentalize it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.13,0:11:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and act it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.13,0:11:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to project it into the world
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.13,0:11:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and think you see it out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.13,0:11:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You own that the darkest part of the id
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.72,0:11:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is a vicious Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.72,0:11:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you own your Komodo dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.76,0:11:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,then under the right circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.89,0:11:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll bite him and I'll come back later after he's dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.30,0:11:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,there's within us, all of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.53,0:11:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the base of the id, the old animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.53,0:11:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.57,0:11:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you own yourself during the course of evolution there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.57,0:11:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can be what the males do in wolf things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.38,0:11:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They challenge each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.38,0:11:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They snarl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.38,0:11:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you own the whole animalness of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.38,0:12:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as a so what because you're not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.38,0:12:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you begin to transcend that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.38,0:12:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to project it into the world anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.38,0:12:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When you don't project it into the world anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.38,0:12:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is a safer place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.38,0:12:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You just own that everybody in our society
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,has a human brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.38,0:12:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,With a human brain, the primitive is still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.38,0:12:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just own it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.38,0:12:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, if you're guilty about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.38,0:12:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you repress it and then you project it into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.38,0:12:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what happened with Karl Marx.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.38,0:12:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.94,0:12:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx, of course, would have benefited a lot by Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.50,0:12:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.50,0:12:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we're saying is this is the infinite field, the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.50,0:12:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel stated there is an absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.50,0:12:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All spiritual reality, every state of enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.50,0:12:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,has a reconfirmation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.50,0:12:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We call it divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.50,0:13:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We call it the infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.50,0:13:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The book Power Versus Force, I think, is being translated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.50,0:13:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's being published in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.50,0:13:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,China is still not too happy about religiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.50,0:13:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to transform the word God into the infinite,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.50,0:13:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite power, infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.73,0:13:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So we use secular terminology then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.73,0:13:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll say this is the infinite power source of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.73,0:13:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.73,0:13:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you call it, so you got to cross out God
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.73,0:13:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and just say infinite power source and it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.78,0:13:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.78,0:13:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this is the proximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.78,0:13:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.78,0:13:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said things don't happen by virtue of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.78,0:13:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They happen as potentiality becomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.78,0:13:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,if prevailing conditions are favorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.78,0:13:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If prevailing conditions are favorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.01,0:13:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The seed that's been laying in there in the dirt for 150 years
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.01,0:13:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly shoots out of the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.01,0:14:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,150 years, all the conditions were absolutely perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.01,0:14:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The potential was unaffected by the weather conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.34,0:14:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The potential laid there for 150 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.49,0:14:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, this proximate field, the proximate field was perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.49,0:14:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it came forth as a century plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.54,0:14:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what they call them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.54,0:14:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Century plants?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.54,0:14:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.54,0:14:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we actually asked that about that particular seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.80,0:14:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How long did it lay there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.80,0:14:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,150 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.80,0:14:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then conditions prevail.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.80,0:14:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When the right conditions prevailed,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.25,0:14:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,an African gray parrot appeared in my living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.30,0:14:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.30,0:14:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing caused it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.40,0:14:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing caused it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.40,0:14:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.40,0:14:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The content.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.53,0:14:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.53,0:14:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.53,0:14:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.53,0:14:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's the problem with logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.53,0:14:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem with logic and political discourse
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.53,0:15:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is a statement is made within form.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.73,0:15:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And what they don't realize is that truth depends not just on form,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.91,0:15:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.01,0:15:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And even not only in that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.01,0:15:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but context, again, aligned within the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.13,0:15:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot define truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.13,0:15:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we looked at the great thinkers of the Western world over the centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.13,0:15:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say 350 BC until the present time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.46,0:15:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single one of them would be able to decide what is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.46,0:15:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All the best minds of history cannot decide what is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.50,0:15:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.50,0:15:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're trying to define truth in the here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.75,0:15:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot define truth except within the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.75,0:15:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What time, what place, what level of abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.75,0:15:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And even then you cannot verify it unless you compare it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.75,0:15:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to an absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.75,0:15:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can calibrate it and verify whether you've arrived at truth or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.75,0:16:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thing that we're studying about power versus force,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.85,0:16:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'm just the witness of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.85,0:16:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,was the discovery of how to tell truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.85,0:16:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first time in human history.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.85,0:16:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How to tell it within an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.85,0:16:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then how to convey that to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.94,0:16:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So from a detached viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.70,0:16:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the first time the world has had any
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.92,0:16:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,definition of what is truth that is verifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.82,0:16:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the subject of the book that I'm finishing up,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.82,0:16:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is truth or falsehood, truth or falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.23,0:16:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw the greatest minds that ever lived
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot decide on what is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.48,0:16:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All the greatest minds that have ever lived
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.34,0:16:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot decide on what is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.34,0:16:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we are in a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.03,0:17:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just stated is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.06,0:17:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How long did that take?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.56,0:17:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the mind has such difficulty in thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.56,0:17:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Understanding kinesiology is because
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.56,0:17:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they're used to a complex Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.56,0:17:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and an explanation within reason
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.56,0:17:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And the response, kinesiology calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.56,0:17:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's beyond linearity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a non-linear response.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.56,0:17:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a response to the field, to this field here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.56,0:17:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are only true within certain conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.95,0:17:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are only true within certain conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.40,0:17:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,within the phenomenal world,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.40,0:17:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,within the phenomenal world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.40,0:17:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether a law is just or restrictive
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.40,0:17:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.40,0:17:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,People complain about the restrictions
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.46,0:17:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of current post-9-11 legislation,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.46,0:18:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and they always neglect to mention 9-11.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.46,0:18:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They always miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.46,0:18:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like after Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.46,0:18:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, like Roosevelt was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.46,0:18:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You forget about Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.46,0:18:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.46,0:18:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So that changes the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.46,0:18:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So retrospective falsification of history, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.46,0:18:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is an attempt to justify a distorted statement
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.75,0:18:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and make it look logical by twisting the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.34,0:18:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a certain thing wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.96,0:18:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on when you're talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.59,0:18:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is slavery wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It is in our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.36,0:18:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it wrong in Athens or Rome?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.36,0:18:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In ancient Rome, 90% of the populace were slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.36,0:18:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All the doctors, the astronomers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all the learned professionals,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.40,0:18:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they're all slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.40,0:18:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Slavery was the way human life was lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.98,0:19:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It prevailed everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.98,0:19:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it only disappeared around 1961, I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.98,0:19:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at the urging of JFK Jr.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.03,0:19:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it probably still exists in certain worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.80,0:19:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.80,0:19:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on what era of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.80,0:19:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way business was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.80,0:19:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody suspected it being the way things were
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.00,0:19:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when I grew up in the 1930s.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.00,0:19:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I considered that normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.00,0:19:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Things the way they were?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.28,0:19:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody thought it was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.60,0:19:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way life was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.96,0:19:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So that explains a lot of the things
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.96,0:19:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,people like to make political hay out of.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.96,0:19:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking something, projecting it in a different timeframe,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.96,0:19:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and now doing a make-wrong with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.47,0:19:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The make-wrong, the reason they do that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.47,0:19:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is if you put it in the correct timeframe,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.47,0:19:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the make-wrong disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.47,0:19:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And they don't get to play victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.47,0:19:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Deprive them of being victimized.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.47,0:20:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is only true within a certain context.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.26,0:20:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.43,0:20:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, nothing seems to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.43,0:20:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,except a potentiality becomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.43,0:20:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,when the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.43,0:20:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,when the field is appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.43,0:20:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.58,0:20:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing happens in and of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of that which it is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.58,0:20:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on its appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.58,0:20:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Going from potentiality into actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.58,0:20:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on the conditions in the proximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that potentiality can become actuality at all
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.81,0:20:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to the infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.94,0:20:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.98,0:20:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.98,0:20:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The core of the ego is grandeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.17,0:20:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The core of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.17,0:20:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego thinks it's God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.17,0:20:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks it has within itself the power of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.32,0:20:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, when a thing happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.32,0:20:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it presumes that there's a causer there called me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.54,0:21:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And it takes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.71,0:21:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes the author then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.71,0:21:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It claims sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.80,0:21:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the real difficulty then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in transcending the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.80,0:21:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is its innate delusion of sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.80,0:21:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.80,0:21:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That there is an I that decided that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.50,0:21:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No I decided for that arm to just shoot over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.50,0:21:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It did it by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.74,0:21:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.74,0:21:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're smart,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.74,0:21:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you will catch
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.34,0:21:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.90,0:21:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.90,0:21:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will claim authorship
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.90,0:21:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten-thousandth of a second after it has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.38,0:21:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you catch it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.38,0:21:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in the classic teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.14,0:21:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddhist teaching of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.14,0:21:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to catch reality between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.14,0:21:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.98,0:21:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's prior to thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.98,0:21:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's prior to thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.09,0:22:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you find this if it happens in one ten-thousandth of a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.44,0:22:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds hopeless, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.04,0:22:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But I tell you, look,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.61,0:22:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to catch the reality that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.61,0:22:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,exists one ten-thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.61,0:22:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to a mental event.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.61,0:22:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd say, God, I don't think I can be that fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.61,0:22:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.69,0:22:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.91,0:22:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.91,0:22:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why there are very few enlightened people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.91,0:22:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You can meditate for ninety years sitting cross-legged
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.51,0:22:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and going through all kinds of fancy breathing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.51,0:22:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and eat fancy diets
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.51,0:22:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and it'll get you nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.80,0:22:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One ten-thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.98,0:22:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because you don't know where to look for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.98,0:22:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know how to look for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.10,0:22:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll tell you how to look for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.10,0:22:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Save you fifty-thousand lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.57,0:22:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.85,0:22:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to move on to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.85,0:22:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll catch how to catch it somewhere along here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.85,0:22:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not really where we want to catch it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.85,0:22:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.85,0:23:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.16,0:23:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the witness-observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.16,0:23:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The witness-observer that is faster than the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.16,0:23:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we move ahead to that and we can back up?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.16,0:23:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget where witness-observer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.16,0:23:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have my list of slides here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.79,0:23:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, okay, go back one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.79,0:23:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so this is the observed event, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.18,0:23:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.22,0:23:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.50,0:23:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to get to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.01,0:23:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.01,0:23:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.36,0:23:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,More.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.75,0:23:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.75,0:23:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.81,0:23:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the person reads in the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.81,0:23:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a mistranslation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.81,0:23:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I've spoken to the Buddha about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.81,0:23:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and he affirms me that I'm correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.94,0:23:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's just a mistranslation from the Sanskrit or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.94,0:24:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality that you're looking for is just prior,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.94,0:24:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,just prior to thinking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.94,0:24:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, thinking this is not like billiard balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.03,0:24:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's thinking in terms of Newtonian causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.03,0:24:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody's trying to look between the billiard balls
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.03,0:24:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and catch reality there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.03,0:24:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll tell you, the billiard balls are moving too fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.03,0:24:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.03,0:24:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't make it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.20,0:24:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so where do you catch it then?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.20,0:24:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You catch it just prior to the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.64,0:24:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, prior to the moment of a thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.64,0:24:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.76,0:24:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point in perfecting thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.75,0:24:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because the reality of that which you is,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.75,0:24:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you is?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.16,0:24:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.28,0:24:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is-ness is present reality, so it's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.72,0:24:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you is, is the condition prior to the thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.35,0:25:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the ocean out of which the flying fish fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.82,0:25:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.01,0:25:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to catch God between the flying fish, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.01,0:25:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't, because the mind tries to connect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.01,0:25:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I said last time,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.01,0:25:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,if you see three flying fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.01,0:25:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind projects out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.01,0:25:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,look, the flying fish made a triangle.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.01,0:25:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.11,0:25:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no intentionality between these fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.11,0:25:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This fish comes up spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.11,0:25:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of that which it is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.11,0:25:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ocean at that temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.33,0:25:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And whatever kind of a tuna fish it is or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.41,0:25:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It automatically does what it does
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.41,0:25:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,because of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.41,0:25:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Not caused by anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.41,0:25:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor did this fish cause this fish over here
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.41,0:25:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.41,0:25:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no secret communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.41,0:25:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.24,0:25:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you catch this phenomenon?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.45,0:25:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now your mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.45,0:25:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind isn't thinking anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.53,0:25:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thoughts are going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.79,0:26:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.15,0:26:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so thoughts then are form.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.15,0:26:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my magic wand here?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.56,0:26:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thoughts are form.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.94,0:26:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Gil found this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.94,0:26:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A great find, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.94,0:26:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's worth a fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.32,0:26:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's form, here's thought in form.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.32,0:26:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's the registering of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.57,0:26:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And the recognition of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.57,0:26:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And all this goes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.57,0:26:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And how are you going to make that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.57,0:26:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in one ten-thousandth of a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.99,0:26:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the average person does
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.99,0:26:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is take form and witness form.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.01,0:26:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're watching the mind's thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.01,0:26:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, I can't get my mind to stop thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.01,0:26:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what is it that knows that it's thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.63,0:26:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what knows that it's thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.63,0:26:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you're registering.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.63,0:26:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's thinking because you recognize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.52,0:26:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what's prior to the thinkingness, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.52,0:26:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't know any of this at all
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.52,0:27:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't for the watcher.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.52,0:27:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you're experiencing and watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.29,0:27:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And how can you experience or watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.29,0:27:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only because of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.67,0:27:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So you retreat then.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.67,0:27:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That I'm not the content of my thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.67,0:27:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I must be the witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.67,0:27:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the camera that's seeing this movie going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.67,0:27:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to identify
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.67,0:27:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,now, and as you move back in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.67,0:27:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, if you stay in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.67,0:27:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so your mind says, I'm going to catch it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.67,0:27:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite reality between two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.90,0:27:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind is thinking that,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.90,0:27:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and now your mind is trying to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.33,0:27:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But your mind can't catch one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.33,0:27:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.66,0:27:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What can catch the one ten-thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.66,0:27:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.18,0:27:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here, in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.03,0:27:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you become the awareness that you're the light
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.06,0:27:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which thinkingness is recognizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.06,0:28:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The watcher, the witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.59,0:28:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is faster than ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.59,0:28:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see where on the map we got to catch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.29,0:28:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, come over and we'll research this map.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.72,0:28:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.72,0:28:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try to get in light through meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.77,0:28:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and you go across this Newtonian track,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.77,0:28:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this is capable of moving faster
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.77,0:28:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,than one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.77,0:28:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's capable of it because,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.06,0:28:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, I see, because of the watcher experience here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.06,0:28:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So the capacity is coming from back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.06,0:28:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.06,0:28:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's coming from back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.06,0:28:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, it's coming, oh, I see where it's coming from.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.06,0:28:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.06,0:28:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The watcher witness then
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.06,0:28:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is capable of moving faster than ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.06,0:28:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you use form to try and catch form,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.09,0:28:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not fast enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.09,0:28:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't word that correctly, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.65,0:28:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we come from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.83,0:29:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because I'm trying to save time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.83,0:29:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.83,0:29:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to finish this in five minutes, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.83,0:29:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go back and do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.83,0:29:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so if you look from the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.00,0:29:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the field will catch it out of the corner of the eye
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.00,0:29:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in less than one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.78,0:29:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will catch that the thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.78,0:29:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,are arising out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.78,0:29:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thoughts are arising out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.94,0:29:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of a complete nothing, silence, stillness,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.94,0:29:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,each thought arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.94,0:29:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What a nice, pretty dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.01,0:29:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What a nice day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.59,0:29:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.30,0:29:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that puts it together in sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.30,0:29:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of attractor fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.30,0:29:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it throws it into a sequence so that it's logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.47,0:29:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But the source of it is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.47,0:30:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here, nobody's mind is thinking of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.81,0:30:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If I focus on that level right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.46,0:30:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't hear anything there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.88,0:30:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.88,0:30:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.71,0:30:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.09,0:30:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How come nobody's thinking out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.45,0:30:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because nobody is thinking out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.45,0:30:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of all thinkingness is coming out of a silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.45,0:30:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So you focus on the silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.67,0:30:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk around in the silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.63,0:30:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk around and you become the silence
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.73,0:30:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by identifying with the field
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.51,0:30:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.51,0:30:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So can we back up again to the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.51,0:30:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,field, content, and context?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.57,0:30:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The diagrams?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.57,0:30:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just back up there
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.57,0:30:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because we'll resume there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.13,0:30:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.28,0:30:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So here in thinkingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.28,0:30:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you're thinking in terms of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.28,0:31:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.28,0:31:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.28,0:31:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you begin to realize that intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.53,0:31:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,here's the field of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.53,0:31:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't even happen without intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.53,0:31:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, instead of identifying with this,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.64,0:31:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you would begin to identify progressively with the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.64,0:31:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, this diagram isn't right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.64,0:31:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to do a better one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.64,0:31:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It should really be quite dark here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.64,0:31:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and then get lighter and lighter and lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.64,0:31:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you identify more and more with the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.85,0:31:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the impersonal field out of which all that is arising,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.85,0:31:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to identify with qualities, qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.33,0:31:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So stop being Mary or Sue or JoJo.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.59,0:31:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about two years of college.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.59,0:31:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about all the job and car
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.59,0:31:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.70,0:31:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You just be the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.70,0:31:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You be the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.98,0:31:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can lecture for eight hours
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.20,0:31:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and never think of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.05,0:32:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, what are you going to talk about today?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.59,0:32:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.59,0:32:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know what I'm going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.59,0:32:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's preposterous.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.59,0:32:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's preposterous.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.59,0:32:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But to people who live,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.59,0:32:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that reality is here,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.59,0:32:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems, and they want you to announce
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.59,0:32:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what the lecture's going to be about.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.59,0:32:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How the heck should I know
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.59,0:32:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what the lecture's going to be about?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.59,0:32:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even get here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.92,0:32:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you going to make love
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.70,0:32:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the next time you make love?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.70,0:32:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Or how are you going to eat the next hamburger?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.70,0:32:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know until I eat the hamburger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.70,0:32:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to start from the left
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.70,0:32:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or are you going to go from the right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.70,0:32:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't think about eating a hamburger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.70,0:32:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.70,0:32:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way is simple, quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.44,0:32:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You be what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.53,0:32:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in its expression as the quality that you deify.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.53,0:32:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if that which you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.04,0:32:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,see as sacred is truthfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.04,0:32:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration for others,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.04,0:32:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the openness to see the sacredness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.04,0:33:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and beauty of all life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.04,0:33:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The open sesame to the sacredness of all life
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.84,0:33:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is to focus on the beauty of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.84,0:33:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that exists has within itself
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.84,0:33:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,an intrinsic beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.16,0:33:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't think about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.16,0:33:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you increase your awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.16,0:33:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that, first of all, you just heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.16,0:33:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.16,0:33:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything within it has an absolute beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.16,0:33:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.16,0:33:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everything within it exists
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.16,0:33:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because out of the source of existence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.31,0:33:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is the unmanifest within the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.48,0:33:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first thing that hits you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.79,0:33:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as the ego dies and it crashes painfully
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.79,0:33:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is suddenly the stunning presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.79,0:33:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of the radiance of divinity shining forth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.79,0:33:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,out of all of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.79,0:33:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It shines forth as a stunning
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.79,0:33:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible overwhelming beauty, paralyzing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.47,0:33:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The beauty is so intense that one can barely move
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.47,0:34:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that all thought stops
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.47,0:34:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and it never starts again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.64,0:34:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you have to learn how to function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.63,0:34:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're surrounded by a paralyzing stunning beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.63,0:34:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the moment of the most highest
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.63,0:34:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisite music you ever heard
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.63,0:34:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that made the hair stand up in the back of your head
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.63,0:34:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you're supposed to go to work feeling that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.63,0:34:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That took 30 years, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.11,0:34:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Years.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.11,0:34:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.73,0:34:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, what's going to happen if I become enlightened?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.73,0:34:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's going to look after the kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.73,0:34:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.73,0:34:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the universe's worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.73,0:34:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe will take care of it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.73,0:34:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the quality of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.73,0:34:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,brings to you that which is needed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.73,0:34:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same applies to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.73,0:34:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That which they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.73,0:34:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,by their karmic inheritance,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.73,0:34:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,will pull forth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.73,0:35:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is karmically within possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.23,0:35:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.57,0:35:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you be and reflect that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.57,0:35:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of being a person or a definable,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.57,0:35:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you become a quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.57,0:35:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the expression of that quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.57,0:35:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about learning to love.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.80,0:35:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be love.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.80,0:35:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Love does not go from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.80,0:35:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.15,0:35:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the reason a bird's consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.15,0:35:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or a dog or a kitty,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.15,0:35:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because of the field of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.15,0:35:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the field of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.15,0:35:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,its potentiality becomes an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.15,0:35:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, it stays a wild animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.82,0:35:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So we open ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.32,0:35:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience the intrinsic beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.32,0:35:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.48,0:35:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All that exists in form
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.48,0:35:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,has within itself the formless.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.73,0:36:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.73,0:36:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of the infinite potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.73,0:36:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of the unmanifest becoming manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.73,0:36:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.67,0:36:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.67,0:36:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.80,0:36:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.80,0:36:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.80,0:36:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego would like to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.80,0:36:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I made it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.80,0:36:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't make anything happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.15,0:36:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot make anything happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.53,0:36:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't make anything happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.53,0:36:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can increase the likelihood,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.07,0:36:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,statistically,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.07,0:36:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot make anything happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.07,0:36:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.07,0:36:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,To make means the power of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.07,0:36:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That which it was
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.21,0:36:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,now becomes this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.21,0:36:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's creation, not causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.21,0:36:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Only divinity has the power of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.21,0:36:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.21,0:36:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to claim that you have the power
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.21,0:36:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to cause anything to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.21,0:36:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is a grandiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.21,0:36:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A normal grandiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.01,0:37:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Allah,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.34,0:37:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,great and terrible,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.51,0:37:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to sacrifice maidens.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.53,0:37:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand everything in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.01,0:37:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Time for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.26,0:37:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.65,0:37:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Trampled.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.65,0:38:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A victim of man's brutality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.30,0:38:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.65,0:38:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a veteran now of the wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.36,0:38:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.44,0:38:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We were someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.46,0:38:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.61,0:38:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we had to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.26,0:38:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to transcend duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.26,0:38:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see the worst expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.80,0:38:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of it when it's put into social action.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.80,0:38:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the perpetrator-victim model
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.84,0:38:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is very...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.26,0:38:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't see things as mutuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.26,0:38:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,symbiotically beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.34,0:38:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees things as saprophytic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.34,0:38:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the winner,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.34,0:38:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.34,0:38:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's all in the vision
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.34,0:39:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of res interna, res cogitans.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.65,0:39:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't see things as mutuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.84,0:39:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.48,0:39:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Big company comes to a little town.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.48,0:39:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a little town like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.48,0:39:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Deansville, Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.48,0:39:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Population.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.48,0:39:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Seventy, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.65,0:39:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And the cannery came there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.65,0:39:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you know, in the depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.84,0:39:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no money.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.84,0:39:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So here comes a company.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.84,0:39:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now everybody's suddenly got a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.84,0:39:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they can afford a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.84,0:39:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They can get their teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.84,0:39:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Kids send the kids to the dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.03,0:39:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has a way to take a living.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.03,0:39:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the company,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.03,0:39:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,now makes a profit
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.03,0:39:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because they've got...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.03,0:39:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They went to where labor was inexpensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.57,0:39:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's what's called common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.57,0:39:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,People worry about wages in the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.57,0:39:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, you know who sets the wages in the U.S.?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.57,0:39:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hong Kong.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.57,0:39:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's who sets your wages.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.57,0:39:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about Wal-Mart.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.57,0:40:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not Wal-Mart.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.57,0:40:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Hong Kong.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.57,0:40:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.57,0:40:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's India that sets your wages here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.57,0:40:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have to pay
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.92,0:40:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,$11 an hour in side benefits.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.92,0:40:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of $21 an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.92,0:40:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do it for $10.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.92,0:40:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So to survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.92,0:40:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.92,0:40:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to have to offshore.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.92,0:40:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.21,0:40:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the economy then survives
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.51,0:40:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because it offshores.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.51,0:40:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.55,0:40:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,mutuality is seeing that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.55,0:40:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the company and the populace,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.55,0:40:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the worker,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.55,0:40:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they all benefit mutually.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.55,0:40:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The same things, you know, go on
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.55,0:40:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.55,0:40:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In other ways of looking at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.01,0:40:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.01,0:40:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the book that's coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.01,0:40:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,would not happen without Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.01,0:40:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want you to come up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.01,0:41:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.25,0:41:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Show them what happened to your arm
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.25,0:41:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time we finish the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.34,0:41:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,7,000 calibrations later.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.34,0:41:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, you know, it's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.90,0:41:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it hasn't gone to the printer quite yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.90,0:41:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I'll come up with one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.90,0:41:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And she'll say, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.90,0:41:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.78,0:41:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not men against women,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.78,0:41:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's men with women.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.78,0:41:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the weak masculine derides women.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.78,0:41:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The weak masculine puts down women,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.05,0:41:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is frightened of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.05,0:41:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't want them to have any power.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.05,0:41:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The same cultures also put down dogs,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.05,0:41:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.05,0:41:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, certain cultures, dogs,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.32,0:41:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the treatment of dogs calibrates at 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.32,0:41:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In America, the treatment of dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.57,0:41:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.57,0:41:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same corollary goes on
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.86,0:42:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,how those cultures treat women and children.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.86,0:42:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the strong masculine
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.57,0:42:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,honors and protects women.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.05,0:42:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the weak exploits.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.05,0:42:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the weak is,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.05,0:42:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason you can't take chances with the weak
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.05,0:42:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is because the weak
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.21,0:42:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,savages weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.46,0:42:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It savages vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.46,0:42:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The invitation to disaster
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.65,0:42:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be a wimp.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.78,0:42:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And walk through the inner city.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.78,0:42:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's a different culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.94,0:42:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,has different rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.94,0:42:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to get yourself killed
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.55,0:42:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be a wimp
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.55,0:42:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in a savage culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.55,0:42:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because your wimpism
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.61,0:42:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,attracts the predator-prey response.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.61,0:42:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't resist to savage you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.78,0:43:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.61,0:43:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the strong masculine does not feel threatened
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.61,0:43:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,by the feminine and honors her.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.19,0:43:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, in traditional America,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.38,0:43:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when a woman entered the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.38,0:43:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you stood up out of respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.61,0:43:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't use vulgar, obscene language.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.11,0:43:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Men hung out in the bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.05,0:43:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and women had the family entrance in the rear,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.05,0:43:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,where they weren't exposed to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.05,0:43:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,obscene language, dirty jokes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.07,0:43:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,vulgar passes by drunken men.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.94,0:43:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Testosterone let loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.94,0:43:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Testosterone is bad enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.23,0:43:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but you get the testosterone intoxicated
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.23,0:43:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and put a woman near it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.71,0:44:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.07,0:44:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between weakness and strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.07,0:44:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so vulnerability is attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.57,0:44:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you allow yourself to be dissed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.57,0:44:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in the neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.57,0:44:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you just got yourself killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.03,0:44:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you allow somebody to insult you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.03,0:44:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,without standing up to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.67,0:44:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.67,0:44:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's suicidal to mix them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.15,0:44:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Markeia Quinsberry rules
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.82,0:44:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,on the street will get you killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.82,0:44:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The history of all the great wars
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.30,0:44:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,has been the West,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.69,0:44:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Britain or whoever,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.46,0:44:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,came from Markeia Quinsberry rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.69,0:44:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other side was coming from
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.69,0:44:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,inner city rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.84,0:44:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've told you the story before.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.84,0:44:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, as a skinny ectomorph
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.63,0:44:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with bifocals,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.63,0:44:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.76,0:45:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was getting beat up all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.76,0:45:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so I found a way home
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.15,0:45:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that would avoid the bullies.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.15,0:45:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But once the bullies catch a vulnerable rabbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.15,0:45:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.36,0:45:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally my grandfather got tired of me
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.36,0:45:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,getting beat up all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.36,0:45:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus I was brought up strictly Christian,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.36,0:45:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,turned the other cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.98,0:45:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're never supposed to be aggressive,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.98,0:45:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,hostile.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.78,0:45:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was a good Christian,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.78,0:45:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wouldn't have lived long enough to enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.15,0:45:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So my grandfather McCutcheon,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.15,0:45:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who grew up in northern Michigan,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.15,0:45:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,also traditional America,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.15,0:45:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,says enough is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.15,0:45:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And he took me to Richie Mitchell's
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.15,0:45:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.15,0:45:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And Richie Mitchell was the former
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.15,0:45:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,medium heavyweight champion of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.15,0:45:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a professional gym in Milwaukee.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.34,0:45:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And they opened a new category.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.34,0:45:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't make fly weights,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.34,0:45:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so they opened mosquito weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.34,0:45:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Eighty pounds or under, I think it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.34,0:45:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.94,0:46:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,this stick of a kid, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.94,0:46:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's these huge gloves, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.94,0:46:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Gloves are bigger than a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.94,0:46:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta lift the gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.94,0:46:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I learned boxing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.94,0:46:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, and I learned how to be very fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.94,0:46:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So what was my asset?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.94,0:46:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I was, I made a very small target.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.94,0:46:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.94,0:46:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.94,0:46:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You did not see that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.94,0:46:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither did he.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.94,0:46:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So then he would have a bloody nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.94,0:46:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'd go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.94,0:46:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody left me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.69,0:46:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the boys' choir.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.51,0:46:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a boy soprano.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.48,0:46:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a beautiful church,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.48,0:46:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,boy soprano.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.48,0:46:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we had practice,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.48,0:46:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,choir practice every Wednesday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.48,0:46:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All the guys, all the, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.48,0:46:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we all had the katas with the white thing and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.48,0:46:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, like in a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.48,0:46:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And Wednesday night, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.48,0:46:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we had choir practice,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.48,0:46:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we had basketball.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.48,0:46:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And somebody would always beat me up there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.61,0:46:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So after I beat the first kid up,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.61,0:46:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I didn't beat him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.61,0:46:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I just gave him a bloody nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.61,0:46:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, every bully,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.61,0:46:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave him a bloody nose,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.61,0:46:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they all left me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.21,0:46:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.21,0:46:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I just had to respond strongly.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.21,0:47:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the law of the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.63,0:47:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the law of the pack,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.63,0:47:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the wolf pack.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.63,0:47:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The male who lords his head to the other
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.86,0:47:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,just got himself taken out.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.86,0:47:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, with my newfound confidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.26,0:47:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so I went to visit my other grandmother,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.26,0:47:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,newfound mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.26,0:47:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,nearer to a lower socioeconomic group,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.57,0:47:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and I played with the kids in the alley out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.57,0:47:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the kids in the alley,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.57,0:47:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, challenged me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.57,0:47:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was never afraid of a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.13,0:47:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how I got beat up all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.13,0:47:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'd run away,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.13,0:47:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was too stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.13,0:47:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was too macho to run away,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.13,0:47:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but not an mesomorph enough to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.13,0:47:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, this kid challenged me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.96,0:47:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had my newfound confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.96,0:47:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I get all set, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.96,0:47:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to give him a fast left,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.96,0:47:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with a right cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.96,0:47:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was good with a fast left and a right cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.96,0:47:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One-two shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.96,0:47:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time, you kick me in the groin.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.55,0:48:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do a left jab with a right cross,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.55,0:48:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the basic boxing move
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.03,0:48:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're crippled and hanging out on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.03,0:48:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to get your breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.80,0:48:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you're down, he then kicks you in the ribs
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.80,0:48:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and stomps you in the solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.80,0:48:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.92,0:48:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.71,0:48:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mix paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.71,0:48:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the male and the female, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.50,0:48:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,are not competitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.50,0:48:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They're symbiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.88,0:48:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The capitalist and the taxpayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.88,0:48:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,however you want to envision it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.88,0:48:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the government and the citizen,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.88,0:48:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, are mutually helpful, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.19,0:48:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You can shift the balance a little bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.19,0:48:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but to demonize them
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.19,0:48:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in a dualistic projection of perpetrator-victim
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.19,0:48:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is the downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.19,0:49:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It sucks in large portions
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.19,0:49:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of people's minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.19,0:49:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I wanted to clear that up,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.05,0:49:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that the upside is symbiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.21,0:49:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's have the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.82,0:49:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just an explanation of that diagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.25,0:49:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're working on a better diagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.25,0:49:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought for the content,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.25,0:49:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,we should have a kitty with a ball
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.25,0:49:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or a dog with a bone or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.25,0:49:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.25,0:49:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,geometric figures.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.38,0:49:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.38,0:49:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is, we call it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.38,0:49:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego and the spiritual ego and the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.38,0:49:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could say
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.40,0:49:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the linear, the semi-linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.40,0:49:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.40,0:49:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the diagram,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.40,0:49:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we have what's limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.40,0:49:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximate field is semi-limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.40,0:49:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the context is unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.40,0:49:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if you identify,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.40,0:50:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not too hard to move from this...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.40,0:50:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,from this world to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.40,0:50:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world of quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.40,0:50:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,non-linear dynamics.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.40,0:50:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with what appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.05,0:50:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of circumscribed and limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.05,0:50:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.05,0:50:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to see randomness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.05,0:50:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see creativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.05,0:50:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a looser field,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.05,0:50:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,approximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.05,0:50:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, of course, the ultimate context here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.05,0:50:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So to move ahead spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.30,0:50:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm saying is don't identify with this,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.30,0:50:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is, first of all, boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.30,0:50:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think you're boring?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.30,0:50:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you're dreadfully boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.42,0:50:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times can you look in the mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.38,0:50:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and still be interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.05,0:50:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I look in the mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.05,0:50:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the same boring image again.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.78,0:50:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting older, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.78,0:51:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.42,0:51:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The personal self and its ambitions
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.42,0:51:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and all is boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.42,0:51:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what is energizing it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.42,0:51:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is the approximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.42,0:51:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.42,0:51:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying to go to college
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.42,0:51:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is going to lead someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.42,0:51:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would a person want to improve themself anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.84,0:51:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because they intuit
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.84,0:51:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is a progression possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.84,0:51:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you begin to identify yourself with
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.84,0:51:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is context.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.84,0:51:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You identify yourself with the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.84,0:51:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The field in which you exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.94,0:51:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of the field, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.94,0:51:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that you choose to value,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.94,0:51:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you see things the way you see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.94,0:51:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you value truth above political positionality,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.61,0:51:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,then you see through the illusions of politics
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.61,0:52:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you wonder how a man's going to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.61,0:52:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The most frightening thing, folks,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.61,0:52:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is to calibrate all the politicians out in the media,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.61,0:52:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.61,0:52:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Our survival is in their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.61,0:52:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will say, as you'll see in the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.09,0:52:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,how would you like to have a brain surgeon
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.09,0:52:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrates at 190?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.09,0:52:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the pilot on your next airplane?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.11,0:52:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You meet the pilot, you calibrate him,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.11,0:52:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,good God, 185.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.46,0:52:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're going to put our country
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.46,0:52:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and our survival in the hands of politicians
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.46,0:52:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrate 180 or 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.46,0:52:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.46,0:52:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We are in a philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.46,0:52:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the downside of...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.46,0:52:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So philosophy is not just an academic exercise
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.46,0:52:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is presuming to present truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.46,0:53:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it presents rhetoric instead of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.46,0:53:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we're the ones, mankind, the population,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.65,0:53:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is who pays the price.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.67,0:53:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They get the salary for their job
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.67,0:53:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we get to pay the price,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.67,0:53:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which is known as death.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.67,0:53:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Death.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.67,0:53:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Which can be serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.67,0:53:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking of Secretary of State Simpson,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.69,0:53:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever his name,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.69,0:53:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who said,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.69,0:53:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,gentlemen don't read gentleman's mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.69,0:53:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I was out at sea
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.69,0:53:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in World War II chasing mines.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.69,0:53:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.69,0:53:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If he'd read the mail,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.69,0:53:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,he had plenty of warning about the Japanese
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.69,0:53:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in Purview 4, Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.69,0:53:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine this guy said,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.69,0:53:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,gentlemen don't read other gentleman's mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.69,0:53:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So he turned down the intelligence reports,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.69,0:53:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which are routine,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.69,0:53:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,went across to this, the Secretary of State.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.69,0:53:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.84,0:53:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we then became blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.84,0:53:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And there we were,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.84,0:54:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,playing Marquis of Queensberry rules
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.84,0:54:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.90,0:54:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.90,0:54:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.34,0:54:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth would take you out of that illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.34,0:54:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.34,0:54:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you now identify with the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.34,0:54:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,identify with the field
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.34,0:54:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the content of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.42,0:54:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,then the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.42,0:54:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,without any kind of doubt,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.51,0:54:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,without any kind of doingness such as thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.51,0:54:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking is a doingness, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.51,0:54:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,without any kind of a person
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.51,0:54:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,involved in a doingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.76,0:54:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,involved in a duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.76,0:54:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of a me chasing a that,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.76,0:54:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you just become that which you honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.80,0:54:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that which you honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.80,0:54:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Become that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.80,0:54:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Witness it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.80,0:54:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.80,0:54:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,See how it moves and behaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.80,0:54:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I always tell people who are envious of rich people,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.80,0:54:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,watch how they behave and be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.80,0:55:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I make more money?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.30,0:55:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.30,0:55:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Get two jobs, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.30,0:55:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.30,0:55:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubled my income in one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.61,0:55:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,One job during the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.61,0:55:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,drove cab at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.61,0:55:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Double income, simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.73,0:55:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.73,0:55:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a way,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.07,0:55:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you see yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.34,0:55:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,hold yourself as unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.34,0:55:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold yourself as automatically,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.34,0:55:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,look at yourself like a magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.34,0:55:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of a hungry dog
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.53,0:55:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,going after a bone,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.53,0:55:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,look at yourself as a magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.59,0:55:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,See yourself as magnetic
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.61,0:55:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to that which you wish to attract.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.61,0:55:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.17,0:55:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.15,0:55:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you value,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.15,0:55:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then what is held in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.15,0:56:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What is held in mind as a wantingness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.78,0:56:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to avoid,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.78,0:56:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.78,0:56:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.78,0:56:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you see something because you want it,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.13,0:56:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that tends to repel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.13,0:56:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you see a thing because you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.84,0:56:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,appreciate and love its value,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.94,0:56:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,then it tends to gravitate towards you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.94,0:56:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.30,0:56:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Gravitate towards you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.38,0:56:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you become a magnet then.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.38,0:56:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of a hungry dog chasing a rabbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.38,0:56:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.38,0:56:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You become a magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.38,0:56:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,As a magnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.55,0:56:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have any positionality to defend
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.55,0:56:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore you're not attackable.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.00,0:56:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.00,0:56:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.44,0:56:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's okay to be fallible,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.44,0:56:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you can admit your downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.44,0:56:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Greedy liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.15,0:56:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing wrong with being a greedy liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.94,0:56:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You get elected.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.57,0:57:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We have fun with politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.96,0:57:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a comedy, you know, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.96,0:57:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take politics seriously,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.96,0:57:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're gonna have a bad life.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.96,0:57:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.96,0:57:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.96,0:57:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.96,0:57:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fun game.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.96,0:57:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fun game.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.96,0:57:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fun game.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.96,0:57:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a sport, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.96,0:57:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a sport.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.96,0:57:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the pollsters play their part.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.96,0:57:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's really fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.11,0:57:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So then how you see a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.11,0:57:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is how you begin to experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.11,0:57:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The game is a, you know, life is fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.11,0:57:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an endless game.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.11,0:57:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's incredibly funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.13,0:57:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to keep a straight face
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.13,0:57:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.13,0:57:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so people won't get upset
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.13,0:57:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're laughing at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.82,0:57:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to keep a straight face
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.48,0:57:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see things in a certain way.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.48,0:57:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, you become impersonal,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.69,0:57:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but not impersonal in the way
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.86,0:57:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,people understand impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.86,0:57:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Not impersonal, you become nonpersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.86,0:58:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonpersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.86,0:58:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you're the focus
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.11,0:58:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of a certain energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.11,0:58:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And by holding in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.11,0:58:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you envision as desirable,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.11,0:58:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you tend to begin to reflect that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.11,0:58:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of a separate individual person,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.38,0:58:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you're really only the reflection
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.38,0:58:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of a field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.38,0:58:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.78,0:58:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're like a little mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.86,0:58:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in which this field of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.86,0:58:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which you have now accessed
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.86,0:58:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,by freedom of the will.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.86,0:58:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the freedom of the will, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.86,0:58:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is to choose that with which you identify
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.86,0:58:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,by that which you value.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.11,0:58:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you value is highly,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.11,0:58:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,highly valuable,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.34,0:58:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you tend to become.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.34,0:58:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you picture yourself, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.42,0:58:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as easygoing, lovable, attractive, friendly,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.78,0:58:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and obviously the universe is going to take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.78,0:58:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.73,0:59:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you starve to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.73,0:59:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll be pleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.63,0:59:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been under terrible circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.63,0:59:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I was ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.11,0:59:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the truck's on fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.11,0:59:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,10 miles from any place,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.11,0:59:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've got no water.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.30,0:59:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.40,0:59:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go, you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.65,0:59:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then, the thought came to mind
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.71,0:59:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to take this much coffee
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.71,0:59:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the bottom of the thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.71,0:59:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,punch a hole in the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.71,0:59:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of the glove compartment of the old truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.71,0:59:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have the old truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.71,0:59:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have the hole in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.07,0:59:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You pour it through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.67,0:59:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no way for the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.67,0:59:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind, to know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.67,0:59:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, it went,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.67,0:59:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and the source of the electrical fire went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.67,0:59:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The smoke cleared away.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.90,0:59:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sort of disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.90,0:59:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I could leave the world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.05,0:59:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,without feeling guilty at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.05,0:59:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.05,0:59:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the perfect setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.07,0:59:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then this voice said,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.94,0:59:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,take the cup and pour the water in.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.94,1:00:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, a pal like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.94,1:00:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Who needs a pal like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.94,1:00:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a guiltless exit
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.51,1:00:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with no karmic consequences.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.51,1:00:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And this voice says,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.51,1:00:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,pour that in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.51,1:00:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.51,1:00:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.86,1:00:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why I'm still here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.86,1:00:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So this field of thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.75,1:00:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so this field is knowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.75,1:00:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pulled to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.75,1:00:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's timeless.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.75,1:00:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.75,1:00:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to create something new.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.75,1:00:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very general knowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.75,1:00:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a subjective state.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.75,1:00:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a spiritual state.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.75,1:00:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists in and of itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.75,1:00:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and it only waits for you to call upon it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.75,1:00:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It only waits for you to call upon it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.75,1:00:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So the efficacy of prayer
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.75,1:00:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is really you're calling in a certain field,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.75,1:00:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,are you not?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.75,1:00:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.75,1:00:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the prayer is by their wantingness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.75,1:00:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing themselves as separate and individual
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.75,1:00:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of thanking God
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.75,1:00:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for something they ask Him for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.75,1:01:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's see the next exciting slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.98,1:01:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, spiritual foundation.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.98,1:01:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these are things which are,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.38,1:01:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it's currently fashionable to vilify,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.38,1:01:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but they are, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.38,1:01:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the very basis of spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.42,1:01:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,To be,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.42,1:01:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and this was traditional America.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.42,1:01:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where I thought everybody was.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.42,1:01:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody acted normal.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.42,1:01:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was orderly.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.42,1:01:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You picked up after yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.42,1:01:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody lived up to ideals as best they could.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.42,1:01:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was friendly,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.42,1:01:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,polite,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.42,1:01:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,cordial,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.42,1:01:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,reliable.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.42,1:01:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You lent somebody something,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.42,1:01:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they gave it back to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.13,1:01:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,People tried to be thoughtful
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.13,1:01:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and tolerant,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.13,1:01:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,easygoing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.13,1:01:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So these were the,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.13,1:01:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the basics of,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.13,1:01:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly, being a Boy Scout
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.13,1:01:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or a Girl Scout,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.13,1:01:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,4-H club.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.13,1:01:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the basics of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.13,1:01:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is what we send our kids,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.13,1:01:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,hoping they will learn.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.13,1:01:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what we think they're going to get at school.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.13,1:01:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.13,1:02:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How to be sane, fair, ethical, balanced,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.13,1:02:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.13,1:02:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.13,1:02:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I think one of the best ways to teach
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.28,1:02:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is to share,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.28,1:02:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, all I do is share my own sense of humor,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.28,1:02:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because those thoughts just come out of nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.28,1:02:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.28,1:02:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they knock me over because they're so funny,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.28,1:02:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got to share them just because they're so funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.28,1:02:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But they just come out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.28,1:02:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be driving along the highway,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.28,1:02:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the most funny thing will come along.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.28,1:02:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,God, where'd that come from?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.28,1:02:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.44,1:02:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, humor is close to divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.53,1:02:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't know if God stays serious long enough
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.53,1:02:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to worry about the world, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.61,1:02:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But everything is sort of comical.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.69,1:02:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.90,1:02:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We all try to,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.90,1:02:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody who's,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.90,1:02:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,be faithful,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.90,1:02:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.90,1:02:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, faithfulness is another interesting thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.90,1:02:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because faithful means to persist,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.90,1:02:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to persist with a positive attitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.90,1:02:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people do spiritual work sporadically,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.90,1:03:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because they haven't got time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.98,1:03:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to what?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.98,1:03:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to read the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.98,1:03:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you reading the book
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.09,1:03:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're doing spiritual work?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.09,1:03:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't got time to meditate.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.17,1:03:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wasting time meditating
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.17,1:03:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're interested in spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.17,1:03:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work is a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.25,1:03:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.30,1:03:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Be holy now?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.30,1:03:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.30,1:03:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.30,1:03:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you get in your car,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.30,1:03:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,right back to,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.30,1:03:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,oh,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.30,1:03:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what we call reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.30,1:03:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is non-reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.30,1:03:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.73,1:03:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.75,1:03:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And we get back in the car,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.75,1:03:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we call that reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.75,1:03:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, spiritual work gets separated from life,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.57,1:03:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,through finesse,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.57,1:03:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to finesse the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.65,1:03:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of enlightenment then.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.15,1:03:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really almost like a finesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.21,1:03:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a finesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.21,1:03:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a going after.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.21,1:03:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a doingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.21,1:03:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a performance.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.21,1:03:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.01,1:04:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That being pulls to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.01,1:04:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the answer to a thing
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.01,1:04:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is found not by asking a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.01,1:04:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer to a thing is
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.34,1:04:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,found by holding
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.34,1:04:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,something in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.34,1:04:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You just hold it in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.59,1:04:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.59,1:04:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're supplicating
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.59,1:04:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.59,1:04:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.42,1:04:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from supplication.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.42,1:04:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're coming from a humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.42,1:04:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Your humility is a way of being
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.26,1:04:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.26,1:04:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not an artificiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.30,1:04:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.92,1:04:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty of all things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.17,1:04:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty of all things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.59,1:04:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the beauty of all things?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.78,1:04:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you just hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.78,1:04:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.05,1:04:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that intrinsic to all that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.05,1:04:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is a beauty of stunning,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.05,1:04:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a stunning beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.05,1:04:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Stunning.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.05,1:04:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't look at anything
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.05,1:04:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and still function.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.05,1:04:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very hard.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.05,1:05:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.05,1:05:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The beauty of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.05,1:05:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The texture.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.34,1:05:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The geometric form.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.34,1:05:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.30,1:05:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The allness of it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.30,1:05:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.30,1:05:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.61,1:05:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing comes into existence
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.61,1:05:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,except by virtue of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.84,1:05:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.84,1:05:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,within the manifest,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.84,1:05:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what you're witnessing,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.88,1:05:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is the unmanifest
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.90,1:05:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,which radiates forth
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.90,1:05:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.90,1:05:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you first see it,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.90,1:05:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you just go,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.90,1:05:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking at God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.05,1:05:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,God expressed in form.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.44,1:05:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.44,1:05:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, people look at form.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.30,1:05:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't see the beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.30,1:05:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't sense
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.30,1:05:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence within.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.30,1:05:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're busy looking for God
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.57,1:05:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,someplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.57,1:05:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.84,1:05:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that is an awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.19,1:06:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.19,1:06:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.73,1:06:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're seeing beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.73,1:06:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as one of the attributes of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.07,1:06:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty, like love,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.07,1:06:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,are the attributes of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.26,1:06:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.26,1:06:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to love all that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.26,1:06:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is simple
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.26,1:06:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because one sees
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.26,1:06:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the exquisite beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.26,1:06:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.26,1:06:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very hard
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.26,1:06:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to let go
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.46,1:06:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of a nice old piece of wood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.46,1:06:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got lots of them
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.46,1:06:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,around the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.46,1:06:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Boxes of nice old
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.46,1:06:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,pieces of wood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.67,1:06:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very hard
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.67,1:06:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to let go
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.67,1:06:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of a nice old piece of wood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.67,1:06:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got lots of them
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.67,1:06:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,around the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.67,1:06:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Boxes of nice old
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.86,1:06:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,pieces of wood
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.23,1:06:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that are so aged
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.23,1:06:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and twisted sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.23,1:06:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and like
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.50,1:06:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this little piece of wood
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.50,1:06:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,just lays there
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.50,1:06:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,all sort of crumpled up
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.50,1:06:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in 50 years of rain,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.94,1:06:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.94,1:06:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's just
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.94,1:06:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the most impossible
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.94,1:06:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to throw it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.17,1:06:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you see
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.34,1:06:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the intrinsic beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.34,1:07:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.96,1:07:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, out of this
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.73,1:07:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,way of being in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.73,1:07:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,faithfulness is automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.73,1:07:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Loyalty is automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.73,1:07:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All these qualities
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.73,1:07:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,are automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.73,1:07:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.73,1:07:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to pursue them
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.73,1:07:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because your attitude
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.82,1:07:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,towards that
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.82,1:07:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which is beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.82,1:07:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.82,1:07:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.05,1:07:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.09,1:07:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.09,1:07:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the intrinsic value
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.09,1:07:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.09,1:07:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.55,1:07:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,all these other things
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.55,1:07:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,being diplomatic,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.65,1:07:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to be diplomatic
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.65,1:07:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and not hurt
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.65,1:07:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,other people's feelings,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.65,1:07:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,all these come out
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.65,1:07:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of the way
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.65,1:07:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.65,1:07:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,To see the sacredness
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.65,1:07:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.65,1:07:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.53,1:07:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.53,1:07:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.53,1:07:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of seeing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.53,1:07:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you don't get it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.53,1:07:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by asking a question
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.53,1:07:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because a question
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.53,1:07:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is already a linearity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.17,1:07:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're looking for
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.17,1:07:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is a non-linear
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.17,1:07:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding-ness,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.17,1:08:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehension,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.17,1:08:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.17,1:08:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.17,1:08:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you ask a question,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.17,1:08:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you just put it
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.17,1:08:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,into the limitation
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.17,1:08:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of form.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.17,1:08:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you're talking
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.40,1:08:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a dualistic ego
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.40,1:08:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of language.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.40,1:08:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.40,1:08:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a dualistic ego
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.40,1:08:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of language.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.07,1:08:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.07,1:08:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a dualistic ego
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.07,1:08:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of language.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.07,1:08:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,God, what does
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.07,1:08:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so and so mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.07,1:08:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you expect?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.07,1:08:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A voice to come out
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.07,1:08:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of the heavens
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.07,1:08:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and says it means
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.07,1:08:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you're no good, kid?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.07,1:08:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.90,1:08:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.90,1:08:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when you hold
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.90,1:08:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,something in mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.90,1:08:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.90,1:08:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.90,1:08:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Purusha
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.90,1:08:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,within.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.90,1:08:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.90,1:08:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.90,1:08:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,within.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.90,1:08:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The all knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.40,1:08:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,within.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.40,1:08:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.69,1:08:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,like,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.69,1:08:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,illuminates
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.69,1:08:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.69,1:08:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,effortlessly
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.69,1:08:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,within.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.69,1:08:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.69,1:08:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.02,1:08:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,different
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.02,1:08:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,than something
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.02,1:08:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that is already
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.02,1:08:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,within you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.02,1:08:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.02,1:08:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.02,1:08:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,an otherness
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.02,1:08:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,coming to a thisness,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.02,1:08:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.88,1:08:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,dualistic way
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.88,1:09:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of holding it
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.88,1:09:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.88,1:09:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and limits
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.32,1:09:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.32,1:09:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You become
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.32,1:09:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.32,1:09:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You become
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.32,1:09:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that which
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.32,1:09:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is positive,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.32,1:09:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasant,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.32,1:09:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,sensible,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.35,1:09:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,grateful
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.35,1:09:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for all of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.35,1:09:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,protective
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.35,1:09:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,towards that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.35,1:09:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.38,1:09:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The strong
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.38,1:09:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,protect the weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.73,1:09:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The weak
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.73,1:09:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the back
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.86,1:09:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,alleys.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.86,1:09:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The savage
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.47,1:09:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.47,1:09:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The savage
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.47,1:09:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.47,1:09:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The savage
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.47,1:09:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the women,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.67,1:09:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the children,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.67,1:09:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the dogs,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.67,1:09:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.67,1:09:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,skinny ectomorphs.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.69,1:09:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.69,1:09:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.69,1:09:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.69,1:09:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,become loyal
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.69,1:09:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because there is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.69,1:09:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a lovingness
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.69,1:09:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,towards all
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.69,1:09:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.69,1:09:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.69,1:09:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you and a
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.69,1:09:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,parrot,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.69,1:09:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.69,1:09:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you and your
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.69,1:09:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,comrades at
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.85,1:09:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,arms,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.85,1:09:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.85,1:09:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,one you see
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.85,1:09:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that after
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.85,1:09:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,great catastrophes,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.85,1:09:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.85,1:09:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,after 9-11,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.85,1:09:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.85,1:10:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,fire department,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.85,1:10:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the police department,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.85,1:10:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the mayor,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.85,1:10:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole town
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.85,1:10:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,comes together.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.85,1:10:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a coming
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.85,1:10:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,togetherness,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.85,1:10:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,a coming
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.85,1:10:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,togetherness
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.85,1:10:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and bravery
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.85,1:10:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that shows up
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.85,1:10:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,under those
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.85,1:10:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstances
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.85,1:10:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.85,1:10:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,forgets their
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.85,1:10:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,personal
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.85,1:10:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,selfishness
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.85,1:10:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for a change.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.96,1:10:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.96,1:10:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.96,1:10:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and war,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.96,1:10:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.96,1:10:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the ambiance
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.96,1:10:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.96,1:10:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,like in
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.96,1:10:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.96,1:10:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was a oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.96,1:10:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You could go out
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.96,1:10:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and hitchhike
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.96,1:10:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and get a ride
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.96,1:10:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.96,1:10:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody locked
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.96,1:10:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,their doors.
