Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.92,1:23:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because I love animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.35,1:23:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.22,1:23:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks like an animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.93,1:23:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If it sees something weak, it will savage it
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.39,1:23:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because the predator-prey response
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.22,1:23:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is automatic in the animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.80,1:23:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We see it on the streets of the inner city.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.13,1:23:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The left brain, you see the stimulus,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.93,1:23:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the input comes in through the relay center.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.86,1:23:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fast to the emotional center.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.85,1:23:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the emotional center.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.50,1:23:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the input then is slow.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.07,1:23:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the prefrontal cortex to the emotional center.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.55,1:23:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the memory of this gets stored back here.
