Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.85,1:26:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or Yale, I forget where.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.42,1:26:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They were researching finding consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.19,1:27:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,within the neurotransmitter system.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.82,1:27:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.43,1:27:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Francis, not too long ago, said that the success
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.31,1:27:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of this research, I calibrated that research.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.52,1:27:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He said about 140.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.59,1:27:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell you where it's going to go before he starts it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.93,1:27:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrated it 140 to prove that, he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.32,1:27:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind after this research, mankind will no longer believe
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.43,1:27:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in the afterlife of the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.80,1:27:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as long as he stuck to science, he was in his own field.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.39,1:27:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That research was at 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.39,1:27:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It was worth funding.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.85,1:27:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, he just wasted a lot of the taxpayer's money
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.89,1:27:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because he's going to try and prove that there is no spirit,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.72,1:27:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.31,1:27:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And after he finishes his research,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.72,1:27:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,man will be convinced that there is no soul and no afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.03,1:27:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Francis went over just a couple weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.07,1:28:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, the pressure's on.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.18,1:28:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.19,1:28:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.50,1:28:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.80,1:28:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.00,1:28:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.64,1:28:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're going to make a statement.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.14,1:28:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Francis was glad and happy to find he was wrong, resisting.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.31,1:28:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the reason I had permission to do that is
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.75,1:28:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because he felt a little guilty as he went out,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.94,1:28:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,God almighty, misleading people.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.96,1:28:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I got it from him.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.55,1:28:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But I got that he was like, pow.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.31,1:28:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he got me focusing in on it and I'm getting like an okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.98,1:28:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So, he discovered the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.59,1:28:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.98,1:28:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of heart, he wants to convey that he was happy
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.06,1:29:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and surprised as he went out of body.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.40,1:29:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Transcended the intellect, went through the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.68,1:29:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll get together before we both come back again, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.97,1:29:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.97,1:29:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now the right brain, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.18,1:29:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is you have an etheric brain
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.43,1:29:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the etheric brain is very fast, very fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.65,1:29:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I send an electronic message through a computer chip
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.46,1:29:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the same time, one through the old-fashioned,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.26,1:29:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,vacuum tube, the one that goes through the computer switch
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.65,1:29:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,will have been there a week or two before it gets
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.60,1:29:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,through the old vacuum tube.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.39,1:29:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the old radio, we used to have vacuum tubes all over.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.73,1:29:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, they were limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.23,1:29:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the right brain, the etheric brain then,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.07,1:29:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,can pick up the complexity of a whole field.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.31,1:29:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It can, it doesn't deal in a linear fashion.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.05,1:29:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, to become the field of that which you value,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.97,1:29:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you see the innate sacredness,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.97,1:30:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that then automatically pulls to you from the non-linear,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.77,1:30:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from the non-linear, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.25,1:30:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How to become enlightened is to transcend the intellect
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.35,1:30:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mind, well, that's the linear world.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.60,1:30:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you have to move to the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.72,1:30:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm telling you the shortcut, you don't have to work
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.69,1:30:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,through all the fallacies of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.30,1:30:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take you another 40, 50, 100 years
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.10,1:30:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and 36 more incarnations to move beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.60,1:30:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the slow way, it's the slow way.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.47,1:30:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't work too well.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.68,1:30:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No. You bypass the whole phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.81,1:30:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that which you know is an aspect of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.22,1:30:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The aspects of divinity are infinite mercy, infinite love,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.67,1:30:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,patience, gentleness, beauty, the appreciation
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.85,1:30:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of all those qualities, to see the sacredness of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.93,1:31:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that all life is equally sacred, whether it's a bird,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.06,1:31:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,tapping to you, trying to establish some kind of a contact,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.97,1:31:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's a mother with children.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.68,1:31:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the same divinity, the same sacredness of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.68,1:31:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to hold the sacredness.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.01,1:31:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the beauty of life and the sacredness are very entwined.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.44,1:31:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see them almost simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.22,1:31:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And because there are qualities of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.13,1:31:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they shine forth of their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.42,1:31:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to look for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.31,1:31:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the beauty of what is there.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.31,1:31:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't even try it, because everything will look ugly.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.19,1:31:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No. You drive it away by desiring it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.22,1:31:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What you do is you see its sacredness,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.90,1:31:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and you value it because of its sacredness.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.22,1:31:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the sacredness of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.00,1:31:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see it, it is then hard to talk or function.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.75,1:32:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So I better stop talking about it, because it wipes you out.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.06,1:32:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It wipes you out.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.23,1:32:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So the etheric brain is very fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.30,1:32:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the spiritual intention as a reading.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.30,1:32:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You read it, just like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.03,1:32:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And instantly, it goes through here and now.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.93,1:32:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stored in your hippocampus as a memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.10,1:32:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Right brain dominance is nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.19,1:32:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's peaceful. It supports life.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.18,1:32:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Increases killer cells from the thymic gland.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.47,1:32:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Increases immunity and healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.88,1:32:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Balances the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.81,1:32:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that it's a different way of experiencing life.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.52,1:32:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a good reason not to be judgmental
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.68,1:32:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about those who are impaired.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.68,1:32:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They're stuck with this way of processing,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.03,1:32:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've been blessed with this.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.06,1:32:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you weren't blessed with this,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.06,1:32:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't be at a lecture like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.06,1:33:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it allows you to make mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.47,1:33:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how I get through from morning till night.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.96,1:33:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because if it wasn't for Susan, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.60,1:33:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going down the...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.60,1:33:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean the wrong way of the story?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.57,1:33:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going down the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.57,1:33:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They all have their headlights coming in our lane.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.57,1:33:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.57,1:33:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's a hint, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.43,1:33:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Just say, let me drive.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.43,1:33:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can drive, Heinz.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.46,1:33:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all right. I'll drive.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.68,1:33:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so I realized that when you get way over
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.68,1:33:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in this side here, I don't know which is the top
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.68,1:33:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and which is the bottom, well, above 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.68,1:33:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get too far over here, it becomes less and less possible
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.68,1:33:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.67,1:33:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, you sort of fade out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.89,1:33:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The women will say, well, who will take care of my children?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.89,1:34:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.89,1:34:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let God worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.36,1:34:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they're destined to die or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.56,1:34:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.19,1:34:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't let that go.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.44,1:34:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.44,1:34:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't let that go.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.76,1:34:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you're where you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.60,1:34:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you've got to let go of.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.39,1:34:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to which you're attached.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.52,1:34:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You think they won't survive without you?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.35,1:34:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been surviving for hundreds of thousands of years without you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.35,1:34:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.73,1:34:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.56,1:34:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to skip to 42, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.56,1:34:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We did all these before.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.56,1:34:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,These were just tracking the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.56,1:34:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to go to 42.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.89,1:34:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,22 to 42.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.07,1:34:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.07,1:34:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.67,1:34:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not 42.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.85,1:35:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me look at the numbers again.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.42,1:35:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,42.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.36,1:35:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a lot of what we've done in the last...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.36,1:35:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the last year, we were presenting sequentially the research that we did for the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.46,1:35:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We did a lot of movies, the social problems, war and peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.46,1:35:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We did the Louvre.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.84,1:35:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We did a lot of...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.76,1:35:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're devoted to truth, then you're devoted to truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.21,1:35:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, if you knew what the truth was, you wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.27,1:35:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.52,1:35:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be sitting blissed out in the cornfields someplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.52,1:35:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.35,1:35:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just went through current society and calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.35,1:35:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.35,1:35:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We just calibrated them to see how they calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.51,1:36:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,These are, you know, I get all kinds of things like science and theology from the Templeton Institute.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.53,1:36:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's articles on these various phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.53,1:36:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we calibrate them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.85,1:36:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an article on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.23,1:36:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say, what is the truth of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.23,1:36:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what anti-creation is.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.23,1:36:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What anti-creationism even is.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.61,1:36:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Against creation?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.25,1:36:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What does anti-creationism mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.25,1:36:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.31,1:36:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you don't believe in creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.31,1:36:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.31,1:36:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Anti-evolutionism is the other side of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.35,1:36:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.35,1:36:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So because, as people who attend these lectures know, evolution and creation are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.78,1:36:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution is how creation unfolds itself sequentially to awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.68,1:37:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can't grasp the totality of the infinite time of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.68,1:37:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to view it sequentially.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.68,1:37:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.68,1:37:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A movie has to be taken in frame at a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.92,1:37:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you condense all those frames at once, you wouldn't get the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.10,1:37:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So evolution is God's way of telling us the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.96,1:37:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter by chapter.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.27,1:37:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get the whole story, you don't really care how it came about.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.27,1:37:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.27,1:37:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But the human mind is.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.27,1:37:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So evolution is the way creation presents itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.56,1:37:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.61,1:37:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest becoming manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.07,1:37:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The potentiality becoming the actuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.18,1:37:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't happen in sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.18,1:38:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's perceived as sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.40,1:38:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So what looks like sequence is not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.14,1:38:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a reality but a perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.31,1:38:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no sequence going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.94,1:38:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as in a hologram.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.94,1:38:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk around it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.27,1:38:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that's sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.27,1:38:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk around a hologram.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.27,1:38:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the arm goes like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.97,1:38:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You say that is sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.19,1:38:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk around the hologram this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.19,1:38:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that sequence?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.56,1:38:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the hologram, nothing's moving.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.77,1:38:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All that exists, exists simultaneously in its totality.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.80,1:39:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we think is sequence is a sequence of perception, not of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.88,1:39:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.26,1:39:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.96,1:39:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.96,1:39:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all things we take out of the newspapers.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.39,1:39:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Journals that we get.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.88,1:39:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Advertisements.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.77,1:39:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Newspaper articles.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.36,1:39:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Quarter page ad.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.36,1:39:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Go and see so and so.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.36,1:39:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said, what is all this worth?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.19,1:39:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Biofeedback.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.19,1:39:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's tried that.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.19,1:39:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Bodywork.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.19,1:39:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All these are over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.27,1:39:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That means they're integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.97,1:39:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Creationism.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.97,1:39:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's the belief in creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.10,1:39:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Crystals are sort of neutral.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.10,1:39:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on what you do with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.31,1:39:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Da Vinci Code.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.31,1:39:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole concept of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.47,1:39:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty complicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.47,1:39:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how it goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.47,1:39:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.47,1:39:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Calvary is 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.47,1:39:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus married somebody or other and had children and God knows what.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.73,1:40:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty fanciful.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.06,1:40:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.06,1:40:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The druids come out remarkably high.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.89,1:40:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how come they're that high.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.97,1:40:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of these, as you can see, is a whole research project in itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.61,1:40:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You could spend months researching many of these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.61,1:40:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does Machu Picchu calibrate what it calibrates at?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.61,1:40:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are the druids 450?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.61,1:40:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Weren't they a rather primitive kind of people in a way?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.72,1:40:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They were really into astrology more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.88,1:40:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.88,1:40:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one of these, you can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.88,1:40:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is a subject for a scholar.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.88,1:40:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I presume that people who attend the lectures will get picked up on something,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.88,1:40:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,research it, and give us a report on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.88,1:40:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How come the druids calibrate 450?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.02,1:40:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all individual takeoffs on spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.02,1:40:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Enneagrams.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.02,1:41:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of these things, what happens is they get a certain ooh ooh ooh about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.07,1:41:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,People go ooh la la about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.07,1:41:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the latest fad.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.07,1:41:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's getting their something read.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.63,1:41:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's going for holographic breathing.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.63,1:41:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's going for rebirthing.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.63,1:41:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping up with it is hard.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:18.63,1:41:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a workshop every weekend, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.35,1:41:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So Enneagrams then have their certain.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.46,1:41:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That was just esoteric.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.46,1:41:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here did est?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.19,1:41:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All the old folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.19,1:41:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Any old esters here?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.19,1:41:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Still around?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.26,1:41:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Est was 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.26,1:41:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember that?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.26,1:41:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was the value of est?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.28,1:41:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that you had to own your stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.28,1:41:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to go over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.28,1:41:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to admit the reason you're late is because you decided to be late.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.28,1:41:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't play perpetrator-victim game with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.28,1:41:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, 400 is a very high number.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.28,1:42:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, 400, you're above the vast majority of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.28,1:42:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When we said that 85% of,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.35,1:42:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,people on the planet calibrate below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.57,1:42:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then what percentage ever gets beyond even 400?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.15,1:42:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So est certainly was very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.15,1:42:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ethical culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.96,1:42:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about Falun Gong.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.96,1:42:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Feng Shui was a disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.96,1:42:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We redid it over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.96,1:42:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, we had to remove all these damn mirrors and pools and ponds.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.96,1:42:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.32,1:42:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.31,1:42:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it started out as a good thing and it got knocked over or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.31,1:42:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.31,1:42:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do Feng Shui.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.89,1:42:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The numbers we've gotten before are correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.89,1:42:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me why.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.09,1:42:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, maybe because, oh, it's sort of in a way dealing with magic in a way or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.09,1:42:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's sort of dealing with magic or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.09,1:42:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I was very disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.09,1:43:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we moved all the mirrors and put the pond back where it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.09,1:43:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It cost me $4,000 to move this goddamn pond from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.38,1:43:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the energy flow down would be correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.38,1:43:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, that's when my back went out when I moved it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.01,1:43:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was doing fine when the energies were screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.72,1:43:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.26,1:43:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.26,1:43:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Freemasonry, of course, has a very big history.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.26,1:43:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the signers of the Declaration of Independence and most of the, many of the presidents.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.68,1:43:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Fundamentalism is just anything that ends in "-ism," usually calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.68,1:43:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of fundamentalism, you've got the 200 beyond me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.68,1:43:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, most things that end up as "-ism," means a positionality about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.68,1:43:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean the reality to which you're referring.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.68,1:43:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you've made a thing about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.68,1:43:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't spiritual, it's spiritual "-ism."
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.47,1:44:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you turn a thing into an "-ism," you've just brought it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.47,1:44:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And religions have done that over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.64,1:44:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You turn it into an "-ism."
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.64,1:44:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it's an "-ism," now it's a basis for war, conflict, revolution, murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.64,1:44:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatha yoga is, of course, very positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.05,1:44:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all very positive things.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.31,1:44:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligent design is sort of a, what is it, secular substitute for God or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.60,1:44:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in religion and theology news, which I read because I thought I should stay up with what's happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.10,1:44:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.32,1:44:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Kirlian photography, which was a fun thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.32,1:44:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to throw in my Kirlian photography box.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.93,1:44:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got Kirlian photographs at my fingertips from back in the 60s.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.38,1:44:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very big back in the 60s.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.38,1:44:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody had a Kirlian photography box.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.38,1:44:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And you looked at your aura, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.47,1:44:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.47,1:44:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then people would read the aura.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.47,1:45:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Pink means you're so-and-so and green means you're so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.47,1:45:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it all calibrates to 160, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.47,1:45:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was disappointed in that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.89,1:45:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, heck.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.96,1:45:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Kung fu, 410.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.21,1:45:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Metaphysics, 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.21,1:45:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Numerology, 210, higher than I thought it would be.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.39,1:45:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Qigong, I'm rebirthing.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.39,1:45:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Rolfing.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.78,1:45:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody been wolfed?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.78,1:45:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.78,1:45:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can stand up straighter.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.88,1:45:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can say, look, he's half an inch taller.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.71,1:45:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.25,1:45:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, those are all fun things.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.82,1:45:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Rosicrucians, soul midwifery.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.82,1:45:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, should you let go of wanting to control a thing or surrender it to God?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.82,1:45:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes a big difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.21,1:45:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,One is secular and the other is secular.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.21,1:45:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The other is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.75,1:46:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I let go of wanting to control something or should I surrender it to God?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.31,1:46:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go of wanting to control it calibrates about four something.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.31,1:46:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrendering it to God is 535.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.11,1:46:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.11,1:46:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Tai Chi at 310 is fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.11,1:46:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Theosophy is wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.11,1:46:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Universalist church.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.14,1:46:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,White Brotherhood, of course, is very well known.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.14,1:46:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The work of Alice Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.14,1:46:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,White magic.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.14,1:46:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,People are always saying, well, it's only white magic.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.14,1:46:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're playing close to the line.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.14,1:46:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just leaving magic alone altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.14,1:46:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,White or any color, whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.47,1:46:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And Wu Den, I don't know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.47,1:46:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.47,1:46:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,These are just things we took out.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.47,1:46:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought people would know what they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.47,1:46:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, there's somebody out there that knows what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.68,1:46:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wu Den.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.77,1:46:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been Wu Den-ed.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.77,1:46:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you might be interested in this.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.15,1:46:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we have to stop?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.81,1:46:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, well, we only got a couple minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.81,1:47:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll have another lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.81,1:47:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What I've been doing this past year is trying to keep you up with the book as we did the research.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.84,1:47:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Reporting the research as it came forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.84,1:47:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lord's Prayer at 650.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.15,1:47:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there's a big difference between om and ah and mispronouncing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.42,1:47:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Om is pronounced oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.42,1:47:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not ahm.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.81,1:47:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahm calibrates like lousy.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.01,1:47:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah-oom calibrates even, I think, less than 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.00,1:47:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.42,1:47:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There's 210.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.69,1:47:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a, I think, Patanjali or whatever his name is, aphorisms.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.69,1:48:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,One of them, translated by Satchitananda, recommends this pronunciation.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.69,1:48:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a translation of somebody, I think it was, by Satchitananda, recommending this sound.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.88,1:48:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see this sound, a-u-m, it's quite a difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.01,1:48:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the enormous difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.30,1:48:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, spiritual awareness can be quite decisive.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.30,1:48:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can spend a lot of lifetimes at 210 and not get too far.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.30,1:48:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And a half a lifetime at 740 and find yourself right in front of the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.31,1:48:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Om namah shivaya.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.31,1:48:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Om namah shivaya is wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.31,1:48:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Om namah shivaya, I think I remember picking that up from Makananda.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.69,1:48:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Makananda, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.89,1:48:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Om mani padme hum.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.89,1:48:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Gregorian chants, japa.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.89,1:48:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jesus Prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.92,1:48:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Rosary.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.56,1:49:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things, they are very positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.56,1:49:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,12 steps of Alcoholics Anonymous at 540 calibrates higher than a great deal of what's on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.17,1:49:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Golden Rule, Transcendental Notation.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.43,1:49:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Walking the Maze, Chartres Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.59,1:49:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you notice all these acts, genuflexing, kneeling to pray, holding one's hand prayerfully.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.77,1:49:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotional acts, turning prayer wheels.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.80,1:49:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, look at those idiot Tibetans, turning prayer wheels.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.80,1:49:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't they ignorant?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.80,1:49:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the devotion behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.67,1:49:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Turning the prayer wheels, burning of incense, the Wailing Wall.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:44.52,1:49:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.77,1:49:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You see then, the power of devotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.42,1:50:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion then, makes anything sacred.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.13,1:50:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And the prayer of Saint Francis of Assisi at 580.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.60,1:50:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is about where you would expect it to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.11,1:50:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Way up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:20.11,1:50:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Have we got time left for another slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.44,1:50:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,People are always asking for spiritual teachers, so we did a hundred.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.88,1:50:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We did a hundred that calibrate over 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.93,1:50:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They're alphabetical, easy reference.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.89,1:50:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Any one of them is all you need.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.59,1:51:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need is one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.00,1:51:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual students, we always pour all over.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.47,1:51:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we get excited about spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.47,1:51:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We read them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:07.47,1:51:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got spiritual friends that go to their house,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.56,1:51:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see they've got probably 150 books at least.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.56,1:51:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.89,1:51:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So these all, I thought we'll find at least 400 in.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.89,1:51:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate over, you know, 460 is really reliable truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.89,1:51:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So we took 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.89,1:51:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We asked the arm, what would be the right cutoff point?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:32.07,1:51:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We got 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.07,1:51:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.56,1:51:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.00,1:51:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you signaling me?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.44,1:51:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that a secret signal meaning something?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.44,1:51:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.51,1:51:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.51,1:51:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you have to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.51,1:51:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.51,1:51:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll quit.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.78,1:51:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:51.78,1:51:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we're going to do questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:56.56,1:52:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the coming year, we'll probably spend more and more time with questions and answers,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.56,1:52:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,more in traditional style for people who are really intensely spiritually devoted.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.75,1:52:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.75,1:52:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got 100.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.81,1:52:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not necessary to find some obscure oddball thing that was, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.81,1:52:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,channeled from the other side about beings from other planets in the future and crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.02,1:52:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you go out there with an UFO,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:27.02,1:52:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to take you to the sixth dimension of the 32nd future realm
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.02,1:52:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can meet Master Bom-Bum.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.76,1:52:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need that.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.43,1:52:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you avoid spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.43,1:52:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.43,1:52:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called diversionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.43,1:52:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Diversionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.43,1:52:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's nothing wrong with it,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.81,1:52:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is diversionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.64,1:52:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible to master all the writings of all these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.64,1:52:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to feel guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.64,1:53:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of all 100 of them, you've only read two.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.64,1:53:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The other 98 are, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.72,1:53:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And so forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.72,1:53:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because once you get the truth of any teaching, you've got them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.72,1:53:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got the essence of all of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.72,1:53:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, I think it's a very interesting list.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.84,1:53:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A very interesting list.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.00,1:53:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of these names are familiar to all of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.00,1:53:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see some of the great names.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.00,1:53:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At 750, the aphorisms, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:27.00,1:53:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And my favorite, if any author was my favorite,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.15,1:53:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it's Huang Po.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:34.15,1:53:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I get Huang Po right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:36.15,1:53:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I get Krishna in the Bhagavad Gita.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.15,1:53:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I just understand it like that because that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.15,1:53:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one will appeal to you at a different time.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.43,1:53:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Different teachers appeal at different phases of spiritual growth.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.43,1:53:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So people say, which is the right teacher for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.64,1:53:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It all depends on where you're at,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.64,1:54:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're up against,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.64,1:54:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of karma you're getting pulled up.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.64,1:54:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the teacher that's perfect for you here may not be perfect for you there later.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.64,1:54:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes people outgrow the teacher and have to go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.34,1:54:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.34,1:54:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.34,1:54:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything else on this?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:16.34,1:54:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we finish it all?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:19.52,1:54:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:20.52,1:54:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.84,1:54:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.65,1:54:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.52,1:54:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I think there's a hundred altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.96,1:54:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:37.59,1:54:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we moving?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:38.59,1:54:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What's after this?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.59,1:54:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.59,1:54:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going backwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.02,1:54:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty-two is the last one.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:49.80,1:54:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to go from twenty-two to forty-two.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.80,1:54:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty-two and that's the last thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:54.35,1:54:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's the last slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.53,1:54:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty-two.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:56.53,1:54:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.23,1:55:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go to forty-two again.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.68,1:55:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's wrong, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:07.68,1:55:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, they got the numbers backwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.68,1:55:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, go backwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.39,1:55:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.39,1:55:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.75,1:55:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.75,1:55:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We changed the slides around, so I want to apologize for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.75,1:55:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I just tell you, the work, you know, it's progressing.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.75,1:55:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We took calibrating levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.75,1:55:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We looked at the world and all the aspects of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:27.75,1:55:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Went through it extensively.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.75,1:55:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Did thousands of calibrations.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.75,1:55:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And now in the last part of the book,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:32.75,1:55:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we're looking at religions and spiritual truth and the teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.75,1:55:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we've left the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.75,1:55:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We've looked at the world to see how it reflects by calibrating levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.75,1:55:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we're moving into religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.75,1:55:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we end up looking at pure spirituality aside from religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.75,1:55:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And that pretty much concludes then what is really a very,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.75,1:55:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the book is coming out.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.75,1:56:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm calling it the first encyclopedia of truth ever written.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.75,1:56:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.90,1:56:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.90,1:56:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:03.90,1:56:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.90,1:56:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we're going to have a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:06.90,1:56:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, we'll have questions and answers and discussions.
